{
  "stem": "17761.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And there were thousands of people, coming from all places, some of them led by Israel-- by-- sorry-- by Romanian army soldiers, some of them just running to find their families, some of them didn't have any objective, but just being there.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And some of them were beaten up.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And some of them were yelled at and cursed at and you name it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And in this mess comes in a new train with about to close to 2,000 people.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And we were looking for someplace where we could be.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And my father said, let's be in this corner.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "We are going to look for some house.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "Maybe we find some empty house, because the entire place was empty, ruined by war, by the flood, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And as we walk in the streets of this Atachi-- it's called in Jewish literature, Yiddish literature, it's called [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "As we walk, we saw that on many houses, destroyed houses, on many walls there are inscriptions, different things, written by fingers which were dipped into blood.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And I remember one of those inscriptions [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "I, Moshe Israel, Ben-- he said also the father, I have it written somewhere-- and my wife Fiege and my children, vengeance-- venge us the murderers come.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "Imagine what-- what kind of a situation.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "We come from our houses, which still where regular houses, regular daily life.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "We come into that mess of people, of events, we didn't know where we were living, and here these messages on the walls telling us what happened in this place when the Romanian and the German exterminated all these Jews.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And they called us for vengeance, that we should take [INAUDIBLE] because of their deaths.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "We were shocked to death.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And my father stood and said kaddish.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
